      <h1>Key Points</h1>
      <ul>
        <li>Effective recovery comes from maintaining balance.</li>
        <li>Healthy Coping Mechanisms help maintain balance, Unhealthy Coping Mechanisms do not.</li>
        <li>Unhealthy Coping Mechanisms include things like being judgemental and </li>
        <li>Unhealthy Coping Mechanisms are learnt behaviours which likely have been developed since childhood.</li>
        <li>Healthy Coping Mechanisms include things like meditating and remaining calm.</li>
        <li>Healthy Coping Mechanisms allow you to develop control over your mind.</li>
        <li>Recovery is a hard process of replacing negative habits with positive ones.</li>
        <li>There are no cheap hacks, only practice and consistency matter to your recovery.</li>
